{
  "stem": "747.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was something to worry about.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't worry about going to Germany, because we figured we will work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But Poland was something else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father probably heard what's going on in camps. not in details.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in camps, here and there, somebody escaped.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And tried to-- one was Mr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Mendel something-- I can't remember his name-- from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He went all the way to [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Zurich. ?] And tried to raise the consciousness of the Jews, that's what's happening.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And sent letters to America and everywhere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But nobody, nobody took him seriously.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was just too horrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think so.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I find out after when we arrived, from his last word to me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I realized that he knew more than he was telling us, what he let us know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a bright, sunny day, and around 10 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were still-- were prayers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made the Shabbat prayers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the wagon, we had a rabbi with us from a nearby town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And all of the sudden, the doors were open.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we saw these funny looking guys with the striped uniform.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Men.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Nazis and them and [GERMAN] quick!",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Get out!",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[GERMAN] And when the Nazi's didn't look, didn't hear, they were telling the young mothers, give your child, give your child to your mother.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Give it to the grandmother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Let her carry the child.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And didn't understand what it is.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So of course, most of the young mothers didn't want to part with their children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were standing first-- as we came down, five in a row.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then a gentleman, if you call him a gentleman.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Dr.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
